WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

00:00:03.637 --> 00:00:04.738
- Five!
- Five!

00:00:04.805 --> 00:00:07.140
- Four! Three!
- Four! Three!

00:00:07.241 --> 00:00:09.176
- Two! One!
- Two! One!

00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:35.202
They've arrived. We'll get going.

00:00:39.306 --> 00:00:42.376
TORINNER, congratulations
on your Hong Kong concert!

00:00:42.476 --> 00:00:44.578
We'll wait for your US debut!

00:00:44.678 --> 00:00:45.712
Hey.

00:00:46.413 --> 00:00:47.447
Hey.

00:00:49.116 --> 00:00:52.452
Thank you, everyone.
Please continue to root for us.

00:00:53.887 --> 00:00:55.055
So cool!

00:00:55.155 --> 00:00:56.857
WELCOME BACK RYO

00:01:02.262 --> 00:01:03.830
Mr. Choi Ki-young!

00:01:03.897 --> 00:01:07.401
Your group's market capitalization
is the highest among Korean showbiz.

00:01:07.467 --> 00:01:08.802
- How do you feel?
- The new group, TORINNER

00:01:08.869 --> 00:01:09.903
is on a roll!

00:01:09.970 --> 00:01:11.471
Please say something!

00:01:11.538 --> 00:01:13.707
Mr. Choi Ki-young,
please say something!

00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:18.412
Thank you, everyone.

00:01:19.079 --> 00:01:22.182
I'm happy to have become
a source of your motivation.

00:01:25.552 --> 00:01:28.722
A bouquet of music to the world.

00:01:32.693 --> 00:01:34.294
Upload the news article
by the evening!

00:01:38.332 --> 00:01:40.801
I never thought I'd have ended up
coming to Korea again.

00:01:42.736 --> 00:01:44.304
She's late, though.

00:01:44.905 --> 00:01:46.907
She called me out, and she's late?

00:01:48.942 --> 00:01:51.545
Hey, old hag! What are you doing?

00:01:51.645 --> 00:01:53.146
TORINNER ARE LIARS! SWINDLER!

00:01:53.213 --> 00:01:55.415
Isn't that Ryo? Give me that.

00:01:55.482 --> 00:01:56.717
Just stop it!

00:01:58.118 --> 00:01:59.553
Ryo's face...

00:02:00.487 --> 00:02:04.958
Hey, you old hag in sunglasses!
What do you think you're doing?

00:02:05.525 --> 00:02:08.095
- Nam Ha-yoon? What is she doing?
- "Hag"?

00:02:08.195 --> 00:02:12.032
Hey, Japanese lass,
you think you can be disrespectful

00:02:12.132 --> 00:02:13.800
- to an older lady?
- I won't forgive you!

00:02:13.867 --> 00:02:17.738
I'll punish the traitor
in heaven's stead!

00:02:25.812 --> 00:02:26.980
Should I leave?

00:02:27.781 --> 00:02:30.884
Idiot! You didn't clean the place!

00:02:31.318 --> 00:02:34.554
But the manager said
I could finish it by tomorrow.

00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:38.759
What, you jerk? How dare you
talk back to your senior?

00:02:39.693 --> 00:02:41.695
Even if you have no parents
and aren't educated

00:02:41.762 --> 00:02:43.463
learn your manners!

00:02:45.265 --> 00:02:46.600
Clean the place.

00:02:57.077 --> 00:02:59.613
Sorry for the wait! Then...

00:03:00.213 --> 00:03:03.650
A toast to reuniting
with our genius producer! Cheers!

00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:05.986
I'm not a producer any more.

00:03:06.053 --> 00:03:07.354
Former genius, then.

00:03:08.055 --> 00:03:10.223
Don't make that grumpy face.

00:03:10.290 --> 00:03:11.725
Smile!

00:03:11.825 --> 00:03:14.027
I know you're happy
to see your girlfriend.

00:03:14.094 --> 00:03:15.896
An ex-girlfriend! Ex!

00:03:16.096 --> 00:03:18.465
Jeez, you're the CEO
of a showbiz agency.

00:03:18.532 --> 00:03:20.300
Don't cause a scene at the airport.

00:03:20.367 --> 00:03:23.437
Young girls nowadays
have no manners, though.

00:03:23.503 --> 00:03:27.874
So, why did you make me come
all the way to Korea?

00:03:29.743 --> 00:03:33.513
The big project
I bet my life on has finally begun.

00:03:34.514 --> 00:03:36.049
- Big project?
- Yes!

00:03:36.750 --> 00:03:39.052
I'm creating a new K-pop group!

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:43.924
K-pop is popular all over the world.
Who could miss this opportunity?

00:03:44.424 --> 00:03:48.628
I'll gather handsome boys to go
on a world tour, and make a fortune.

00:03:48.695 --> 00:03:50.130
It won't go well.

00:03:50.197 --> 00:03:52.399
Nothing will start unless you dream.

00:03:52.466 --> 00:03:55.736
Now, let's go to our dream stage!

00:03:56.336 --> 00:03:57.604
Glad to see you're doing well.

00:03:59.473 --> 00:04:01.775
It's been so hard!

00:04:02.275 --> 00:04:04.044
I gathered handsome boys
from all over Asia

00:04:04.111 --> 00:04:06.179
screened documents, held auditions

00:04:06.680 --> 00:04:08.715
rented an apartment in Seoul

00:04:08.782 --> 00:04:10.784
for the best 30 I selected

00:04:10.884 --> 00:04:13.353
hired vocal
and dancing trainers for them

00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:14.955
spent a year

00:04:15.021 --> 00:04:16.323
to narrow them down to 12

00:04:16.389 --> 00:04:18.759
and finally selected five members.

00:04:19.159 --> 00:04:21.194
Now, all that's left
is to get them to debut!

00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:22.963
It must've cost a fortune.

00:04:23.029 --> 00:04:24.865
About five billion won, I guess.

00:04:24.931 --> 00:04:28.201
That is, 500 million yen.
The whole sum is my debt.

00:04:28.301 --> 00:04:29.536
Goodness.

00:04:30.203 --> 00:04:31.371
But it's fine.

00:04:31.772 --> 00:04:35.842
These five official members
are perfectly handsome guys.

00:04:36.443 --> 00:04:40.013
I would be able to pay off
the debt once they debut...

00:04:41.314 --> 00:04:42.649
That was the plan.

00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:46.486
But...

00:04:47.287 --> 00:04:48.388
What?

00:04:56.296 --> 00:04:57.931
- Wait--
- That wench...

00:04:57.998 --> 00:05:00.300
Park Ji-soo betrayed me.

00:05:00.367 --> 00:05:01.401
Park Ji-soo?

00:05:01.468 --> 00:05:03.036
The producer I hired!

00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:04.204
PARK JI-SOO

00:05:06.273 --> 00:05:07.307
She's pretty.

00:05:08.041 --> 00:05:10.143
Idiot! The only good thing
about her is her looks!

00:05:10.210 --> 00:05:11.978
She's a traitor and a scammer!

00:05:12.746 --> 00:05:13.947
Traitor?

00:05:14.281 --> 00:05:16.850
That woman stole all the members.

00:05:16.917 --> 00:05:20.086
The handsome boys
I spent five billion to gather.

00:05:20.187 --> 00:05:21.755
All five of them!

00:05:21.855 --> 00:05:23.290
Unforgivable!

00:05:23.356 --> 00:05:25.325
Stop it! It's embarrassing.

00:05:28.261 --> 00:05:30.463
What? We aren't taking a taxi?

00:05:30.530 --> 00:05:32.599
Shut up, I'm broke.

00:05:34.501 --> 00:05:37.370
There are many
K-pop billboards, though.

00:05:37.437 --> 00:05:38.505
Yes.

00:05:39.005 --> 00:05:42.676
What's worse is that woman went
to that Choi Ki-young's company!

00:05:42.742 --> 00:05:45.979
Oh, Choi Ki-young?
That's a familiar name.

00:05:46.046 --> 00:05:47.981
Huh? Don't tell me you don't know.

00:05:50.217 --> 00:05:51.852
That boys' group

00:05:51.952 --> 00:05:53.954
- and that girls' group...
- Okay.

00:05:54.054 --> 00:05:56.857
And those guys, who won last year's
Grand Prize in the MAMA Award, too.

00:05:56.923 --> 00:05:59.426
Everyone from Bouquet Music
is very popular.

00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:01.561
The plain, old guy
who was your colleague

00:06:01.628 --> 00:06:03.930
is now prominent in Korean showbiz!

00:06:03.997 --> 00:06:05.232
Gosh.

00:06:05.332 --> 00:06:08.268
He's doing well. Ha, good for him.

00:06:08.368 --> 00:06:10.403
Why are you so lighthearted?

00:06:11.137 --> 00:06:14.708
You made SEVEN SEAS so popular
as their producer

00:06:14.774 --> 00:06:17.077
but this jerk stole them
from under your nose!

00:06:17.744 --> 00:06:21.314
SEVEN SEAS disbanded
in no time, and they all retired.

00:06:22.148 --> 00:06:24.251
Even though they were so popular.

00:06:25.018 --> 00:06:26.219
Choi must've done--

00:06:26.286 --> 00:06:27.854
It was my fault.

00:06:30.023 --> 00:06:32.859
I told the promising young men
to achieve their dreams

00:06:32.926 --> 00:06:35.328
and forced a life of only singing
and dancing on them.

00:06:35.929 --> 00:06:37.797
But I gave up halfway.

00:06:38.298 --> 00:06:40.834
I was the one who ruined their lives.

00:06:48.775 --> 00:06:50.610
Here we are!

00:06:58.218 --> 00:06:59.286
WITH LESSON STUDIO

00:06:59.352 --> 00:07:01.955
DEBUT RIGHT NOW,
OPEN THE DOOR TO YOUR DREAM

00:07:02.889 --> 00:07:05.392
- I see.
- What?

00:07:05.492 --> 00:07:06.793
It's impossible.

00:07:06.860 --> 00:07:08.495
I haven't even said anything.

00:07:08.595 --> 00:07:13.867
You want me to produce the leftovers
of the five selected members, right?

00:07:13.934 --> 00:07:17.504
That's my guy!
We're the best partners!

00:07:17.570 --> 00:07:18.638
I'm not doing it.

00:07:19.572 --> 00:07:21.074
- I'm begging you!
- Hey!

00:07:21.141 --> 00:07:23.877
I must let the remaining guys debut
and pay back my debt!

00:07:24.477 --> 00:07:26.079
Or will you let your girlfriend
become fish food?

00:07:26.179 --> 00:07:28.949
You're my ex! Ask the producer here!

00:07:29.015 --> 00:07:32.052
Everyone in Korea has turned me down!

00:07:32.152 --> 00:07:36.589
Park Ji-soo... That woman blocked me!

00:07:36.656 --> 00:07:39.592
"Do you want to make
Bouquet Music your enemy?"

00:07:39.693 --> 00:07:40.694
She said that!

00:07:40.760 --> 00:07:43.263
None of my business.
I'm going back to Japan. Bye!

00:07:46.066 --> 00:07:47.334
Ten million yen!

00:07:50.070 --> 00:07:51.137
What?

00:07:52.172 --> 00:07:54.808
You were jobless
after you quit being a producer

00:07:54.874 --> 00:07:57.744
and you've racked up
10 million yen in debt.

00:07:58.144 --> 00:08:00.847
Who lent you money?

00:08:00.914 --> 00:08:04.217
Well, that sum
wasn't borrowed, right?

00:08:04.284 --> 00:08:06.619
If you want to return to Tokyo

00:08:06.686 --> 00:08:10.924
clear the debt right now.

00:08:13.259 --> 00:08:14.494
Can you?

00:08:15.195 --> 00:08:16.930
Ten million yen.

00:08:20.066 --> 00:08:25.105
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

00:08:25.171 --> 00:08:29.609
One, two, three, and four,
five, six, seven, eight.

00:08:29.676 --> 00:08:31.211
- What happened to Kun?
- One, two

00:08:31.277 --> 00:08:33.713
three, four, five, and six...

00:08:33.780 --> 00:08:34.814
Kun!

00:08:38.118 --> 00:08:39.219
Kun, are you okay?

00:08:39.285 --> 00:08:40.787
Aren't you trying too hard?

00:08:43.923 --> 00:08:44.924
Trying too hard?

00:08:44.991 --> 00:08:46.226
How can I not work hard?

00:08:46.326 --> 00:08:47.694
We're running out of time.

00:08:48.428 --> 00:08:52.565
No, Yuya didn't mean like that.

00:08:52.632 --> 00:08:53.967
Exactly.

00:08:54.667 --> 00:08:56.836
We don't even know
whether we can debut or not.

00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:59.672
We don't have time to slack off!

00:08:59.739 --> 00:09:01.574
Nobody is slacking off.

00:09:04.344 --> 00:09:06.679
We're the leftovers.

00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:10.850
Now that TORINNER is gone,
this is our only chance to debut.

00:09:10.950 --> 00:09:12.318
Get out if you'll get in my way!

00:09:13.553 --> 00:09:16.389
Kun looks tired today.

00:09:16.456 --> 00:09:19.125
Guys, let's take a break.
Yes, let's do that.

00:09:21.261 --> 00:09:25.465
What's that conceited attitude?
You think only you are working hard?

00:09:25.832 --> 00:09:29.235
Who's the worst dancer?
You are the burden here.

00:09:29.769 --> 00:09:31.204
- Huh?
- What?

00:09:31.271 --> 00:09:33.073
Wait, stop fighting!

00:09:33.807 --> 00:09:36.876
We're doing our best, aren't we?

00:09:37.477 --> 00:09:39.145
Yes. Let's do it once more.

00:09:39.546 --> 00:09:40.613
- Yes?
- Yes.

00:09:43.383 --> 00:09:44.384
These guys?

00:09:45.085 --> 00:09:47.287
Yes. The group is called NAZE.

00:09:48.321 --> 00:09:49.622
Are you serious?

00:09:50.523 --> 00:09:54.394
It was just a small argument.
It's normal for their young age.

00:09:54.494 --> 00:09:55.628
It's a waste of effort.

00:09:56.229 --> 00:09:58.164
Even a random street dancer
is better.

00:09:58.798 --> 00:10:01.101
It's the job of a pro
to do something about it!

00:10:01.167 --> 00:10:04.137
Their level is way too low
even for leftovers!

00:10:05.472 --> 00:10:07.207
- It hurts.
- Anyway...

00:10:07.774 --> 00:10:11.177
You don't have the option
to refuse because...

00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:12.479
Now.

00:10:13.279 --> 00:10:15.915
You paid... Debt... Me.

00:10:15.982 --> 00:10:18.451
Because I paid your debt for you.

00:10:18.551 --> 00:10:22.822
"I can eat today, thanks to CEO Nam."

00:10:22.889 --> 00:10:26.759
"I'll do any job for CEO Nam."
Your turn.

00:10:26.826 --> 00:10:28.862
- I'm not selling my soul!
- Ten million yen.

00:10:28.928 --> 00:10:30.630
I don't fight for nothing--

00:10:30.730 --> 00:10:32.966
Ten million yen!

00:10:33.600 --> 00:10:34.834
Try again.

00:10:35.802 --> 00:10:37.170
It's impossible.

00:10:39.239 --> 00:10:40.240
It's not worth trying.

00:10:40.340 --> 00:10:43.009
I'll find a way to pay you back,
but I'm out.

00:10:48.681 --> 00:10:51.618
I want to dream with you once more.

00:10:54.521 --> 00:10:58.391
I hate the idea of you
throwing your life away

00:10:58.458 --> 00:10:59.993
over something like that, Azuma.

00:11:00.994 --> 00:11:04.497
I want to see you shine once more.

00:11:07.300 --> 00:11:11.604
I want you to take a chance
towards your dream once more.

00:11:16.876 --> 00:11:20.980
Azuma, use your power to help them
stand on the dream stage!

00:11:41.868 --> 00:11:43.136
Just for a month.

00:11:44.304 --> 00:11:45.905
I'll do it with you
for only one month.

00:11:47.407 --> 00:11:49.175
But I'll do it my way.

00:11:49.776 --> 00:11:53.179
If I conclude that it's impossible
after a month, then it's over. Okay?

00:11:53.746 --> 00:11:54.747
Okay!

00:11:54.814 --> 00:11:56.282
- Oh, and...
- What is it?

00:11:57.016 --> 00:11:59.953
We'll split
what we earn properly in half.

00:12:01.254 --> 00:12:02.722
Money-grubber.

00:12:03.823 --> 00:12:05.058
Seven, eight.

00:12:05.124 --> 00:12:06.292
One, two

00:12:06.359 --> 00:12:07.860
- three, four--
- Attention, please!

00:12:09.629 --> 00:12:12.865
Let me introduce
your new producer to you.

00:12:13.766 --> 00:12:14.867
Fine!

00:12:15.401 --> 00:12:19.405
This is the genius producer
from Japan

00:12:20.273 --> 00:12:24.377
Mr. Azuma Jun!

00:12:26.646 --> 00:12:31.217
What do you say, Azuma?
Four Korean boys, two Japanese boys

00:12:31.317 --> 00:12:32.452
and one Thai boy.

00:12:32.518 --> 00:12:35.888
It's an international team carefully
selected from all over Asia.

00:12:35.955 --> 00:12:38.391
Genius?
Have you heard of the name, Azuma?

00:12:38.458 --> 00:12:40.727
I haven't heard of him.

00:12:40.793 --> 00:12:43.796
Right back at you. I haven't heard
about you guys either.

00:12:44.897 --> 00:12:47.333
What's that attitude?
It's our first meeting.

00:12:47.400 --> 00:12:49.269
Yes. For real, we're adults.

00:12:49.335 --> 00:12:51.971
I was born this way.
Complain to my parents.

00:12:55.208 --> 00:12:58.278
Hello, I'm Endo Minase,
their manager.

00:12:58.344 --> 00:12:59.812
Let me introduce the members.

00:12:59.912 --> 00:13:03.516
No need.
My contract is only for a month.

00:13:03.583 --> 00:13:05.218
It's a waste of time
to remember names.

00:13:07.186 --> 00:13:09.155
Oh, sorry, guys!

00:13:09.656 --> 00:13:12.325
He's a bit slow
and has a small vocabulary

00:13:12.392 --> 00:13:13.726
but he's not a bad guy.

00:13:13.793 --> 00:13:14.994
Just so you know...

00:13:17.063 --> 00:13:18.564
I hate pointless efforts.

00:13:20.066 --> 00:13:23.870
Over a million people in the world
aim to become K-pop stars.

00:13:23.970 --> 00:13:27.440
Among them,
around 1,200 can become trainees.

00:13:27.507 --> 00:13:29.809
Then, only a handful actually debut
and can make a living.

00:13:29.876 --> 00:13:31.878
In other words, it's one in 100,000.

00:13:32.879 --> 00:13:35.281
In the harsh world
of fierce competition

00:13:36.115 --> 00:13:39.552
there's no way leftovers
like you can survive.

00:13:41.020 --> 00:13:42.455
It's a futile effort

00:13:42.555 --> 00:13:44.290
and futile struggle.

00:13:45.825 --> 00:13:48.728
You're wasting your lives to pursue
a dream that won't come true.

00:13:49.329 --> 00:13:51.431
Don't waste your precious youth.

00:13:51.831 --> 00:13:53.599
Rethink your decision
as soon as possible.

00:13:54.100 --> 00:13:56.436
What's that? You're going too far!

00:13:56.502 --> 00:13:59.439
Rule number one. No talking back.

00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:02.475
Rule number two, don't be late.

00:14:02.542 --> 00:14:04.410
Be at practice room
ten minutes early.

00:14:04.477 --> 00:14:07.780
Three, practice
for at least 14 hours a day.

00:14:07.847 --> 00:14:11.551
Four, no dating.
Five, no contacting friends.

00:14:11.651 --> 00:14:14.387
Six, no personal
social media allowed.

00:14:14.454 --> 00:14:15.955
Seven, manage your weight.

00:14:16.022 --> 00:14:18.424
Eight, no smoking
and drinking, obviously.

00:14:18.491 --> 00:14:20.426
Nine, do not go out
without permission.

00:14:20.493 --> 00:14:22.362
Ten, no courier delivery.

00:14:22.428 --> 00:14:25.298
Anyone who breaks the rules
will be fired at any time.

00:14:25.365 --> 00:14:28.768
That's all.
Practice starts at 8 a.m. tomorrow.

00:14:29.535 --> 00:14:30.903
Oh, one more thing.

00:14:32.038 --> 00:14:33.506
As you're a team

00:14:33.573 --> 00:14:36.275
any mistake will be
a joint responsibility.

00:14:36.642 --> 00:14:38.478
In other words, if anyone is fired

00:14:39.078 --> 00:14:40.513
this group will disband at once.

00:14:43.316 --> 00:14:44.450
Disband?

00:14:49.689 --> 00:14:51.758
What's with that cocky attitude?

00:14:52.592 --> 00:14:55.228
Is that Azuma guy okay, Ms. Nam?

00:14:55.828 --> 00:14:58.030
He's rude. It's power harassment.

00:15:00.032 --> 00:15:03.536
I'm sorry, but he tries
to assert dominance right away.

00:15:03.636 --> 00:15:05.071
Just like a small kid.

00:15:06.439 --> 00:15:10.410
But Azuma is the only person
who can get us out of this pinch.

00:15:11.210 --> 00:15:12.278
That's what I think.

00:15:13.646 --> 00:15:16.649
Also, he's actually...

00:15:18.885 --> 00:15:19.886
What?

00:15:20.553 --> 00:15:23.156
Just wait and see,
you'll find out soon.

00:15:42.108 --> 00:15:45.011
Don't get cocky
and listen to music, part-time boy!

00:15:46.012 --> 00:15:47.180
I'm sorry.

00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:49.549
You're busy throughout the day

00:15:49.615 --> 00:15:51.951
so I arranged your shifts
as you requested.

00:15:52.051 --> 00:15:53.586
Do your job properly!

00:15:57.723 --> 00:15:58.891
I'm sorry.

00:16:21.414 --> 00:16:25.151
- Darn it. I need to hurry back!
- Hey!

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:29.388
What are you doing so late?

00:16:30.623 --> 00:16:32.425
I just went for a jog.

00:16:33.359 --> 00:16:34.594
A jog?

00:16:36.329 --> 00:16:38.397
- Go back now and sleep.
- Yes.

00:16:42.034 --> 00:16:43.436
Gosh.

00:16:52.245 --> 00:16:54.146
Excuse me, Producer Azuma.

00:16:56.549 --> 00:16:59.051
What should I do to debut?

00:17:01.654 --> 00:17:04.657
What should I do
to debut as soon as possible?

00:17:08.861 --> 00:17:10.563
You played football, right?

00:17:13.633 --> 00:17:16.469
Yes, I've been playing football
since I was a child.

00:17:16.536 --> 00:17:18.804
I knew it.
You carry yourself like that.

00:17:23.476 --> 00:17:24.744
That's why...

00:17:25.678 --> 00:17:28.514
I became a trainee not very long ago

00:17:29.382 --> 00:17:32.585
and I'm not as good at singing
and dancing as the other members.

00:17:35.187 --> 00:17:36.589
But...

00:17:37.456 --> 00:17:40.693
I want to debut as early as possible!

00:17:40.793 --> 00:17:42.995
I acknowledge
your good physical abilities.

00:17:44.030 --> 00:17:47.033
But the skills needed for dancing and
football are completely different.

00:17:47.633 --> 00:17:51.170
You're nowhere near the level
that can perform in front of people.

00:17:52.972 --> 00:17:55.241
Maybe you'll be good at it
when you're old.

00:17:55.942 --> 00:17:58.210
Well, do your best.

00:18:03.716 --> 00:18:05.117
This isn't going to work.

00:18:06.185 --> 00:18:07.453
I need money.

00:18:08.454 --> 00:18:09.889
I must debut soon.

00:18:11.657 --> 00:18:12.658
Money, huh?

00:18:20.399 --> 00:18:23.069
Let this broke man, who drinks
cheap alcohol on the street

00:18:23.135 --> 00:18:25.037
give you a piece of advice.

00:18:26.205 --> 00:18:27.573
I said it this afternoon.

00:18:28.307 --> 00:18:31.243
Only one in 100,000
can survive in K-pop.

00:18:31.877 --> 00:18:35.615
Most people sacrifice their youth
and regret it afterwards.

00:18:36.816 --> 00:18:40.152
Quit while it's not too late
and get a real job.

00:18:40.252 --> 00:18:42.088
Especially if you want money.

00:18:42.154 --> 00:18:44.657
- But--
- Your dream can't fill your stomach.

00:19:02.308 --> 00:19:03.643
It's time. Let's begin.

00:19:04.243 --> 00:19:05.244
Good morning.

00:19:05.311 --> 00:19:07.079
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

00:19:07.613 --> 00:19:09.382
One person is missing.

00:19:09.448 --> 00:19:10.716
Safe!

00:19:11.350 --> 00:19:14.186
- Darn. I made it.
- Thank goodness!

00:19:14.253 --> 00:19:15.588
You're late.

00:19:17.189 --> 00:19:19.125
No, but it was ten minutes before.

00:19:19.191 --> 00:19:20.359
You're 30 seconds late.

00:19:20.493 --> 00:19:23.396
100 burpees and 100 jumping jacks.
Ready, start.

00:19:24.330 --> 00:19:26.832
Hurry up. Do it. Ready, start.

00:19:36.742 --> 00:19:39.445
- What are you doing? You guys, too.
- What?

00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:41.480
I said joint responsibility.

00:19:42.014 --> 00:19:44.183
Burpee and jumping jacks. Start now.

00:19:44.250 --> 00:19:45.885
- All of them?
- Wait...

00:20:01.367 --> 00:20:02.368
Let's do it.

00:20:02.468 --> 00:20:04.003
What's the point of this?

00:20:09.709 --> 00:20:11.043
Ninety-eight.

00:20:11.510 --> 00:20:13.112
Ninety-nine.

00:20:13.746 --> 00:20:14.880
One hundred!

00:20:21.654 --> 00:20:23.022
Finished.

00:20:27.960 --> 00:20:30.663
You cut corners the last ten times.

00:20:31.964 --> 00:20:33.532
No, I didn't...

00:20:33.599 --> 00:20:36.836
Everyone, an extra 100 squats
and 100 mountain climbers.

00:20:36.902 --> 00:20:38.838
- What?
- What?

00:20:39.805 --> 00:20:42.575
Wait a minute.
Aren't you going too far--

00:20:42.641 --> 00:20:44.276
Are you not going to do it?

00:20:44.343 --> 00:20:46.345
He's fired, then.

00:20:46.412 --> 00:20:48.981
If one is fired,
the whole group disbands.

00:20:49.081 --> 00:20:51.917
I don't mind, though.
Are you okay with that?

00:21:17.843 --> 00:21:19.812
One, two, three, four.

00:21:19.879 --> 00:21:21.747
One, two, three, four.

00:21:21.814 --> 00:21:23.449
- One, two, three, four.
- Don't get cocky!

00:21:23.516 --> 00:21:25.584
- The world's level is higher!
- Yes!

00:21:25.651 --> 00:21:28.921
Each individual's ability is high,
and they're glamorous.

00:21:28.988 --> 00:21:31.157
They'll surely be
this year's MAMA Best New Artist.

00:21:31.257 --> 00:21:32.424
Of course.

00:21:32.892 --> 00:21:35.961
I'll conquer the world
with this group.

00:21:36.061 --> 00:21:40.399
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

00:21:40.466 --> 00:21:43.102
One, two, three, four...

00:21:44.136 --> 00:21:47.573
Park speaking.
Thank you very much for arranging...

00:21:47.673 --> 00:21:50.876
the wonderful studio
for us, Mr. Choi.

00:21:50.943 --> 00:21:52.044
No worries.

00:21:52.144 --> 00:21:53.913
As you said in your presentation

00:21:54.513 --> 00:21:57.316
I sense great potential
in the members of TORINNER.

00:21:57.917 --> 00:22:01.754
Especially the boy who just did
a kick step. Who's he?

00:22:01.821 --> 00:22:03.756
What? Just now?

00:22:04.824 --> 00:22:06.826
Oh, do you mean Ryo?

00:22:06.892 --> 00:22:09.295
- Yes, Ryo. He has good talent.
- Five, six, seven, eight.

00:22:09.361 --> 00:22:10.496
- Help him grow.
- One, two

00:22:10.563 --> 00:22:11.797
- Yes.
- three, four.

00:22:11.864 --> 00:22:13.365
But Mr. Choi

00:22:13.966 --> 00:22:16.468
how do you know
he just did a kick step?

00:22:17.803 --> 00:22:20.172
There are cameras installed
in every room.

00:22:21.240 --> 00:22:23.776
I can check the studio
via cameras anytime.

00:22:24.376 --> 00:22:26.145
Oh, is that so?

00:22:27.079 --> 00:22:28.080
It's reassuring.

00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:33.652
It's our mission to send
shining talents to the world.

00:22:35.721 --> 00:22:39.692
A bouquet of music to the world.

00:22:40.960 --> 00:22:42.194
I sent a message

00:22:42.294 --> 00:22:45.598
but it was just a birthday wish
to my childhood friend.

00:22:46.498 --> 00:22:47.533
Is that so?

00:22:48.434 --> 00:22:51.036
- Got it.
- Thank you.

00:22:51.470 --> 00:22:53.839
Everyone,
100 squats and 100 push-ups.

00:22:53.906 --> 00:22:55.107
- What?
- What?

00:22:55.174 --> 00:22:59.678
I told you. Rule number five,
no contacting friends.

00:23:05.985 --> 00:23:08.554
So annoying. It was just a message.

00:23:08.621 --> 00:23:09.989
Joint responsibility. Start now.

00:23:10.055 --> 00:23:11.223
This is ridiculous!

00:23:11.323 --> 00:23:12.591
Basics...

00:23:12.691 --> 00:23:14.894
We've only been doing
pointless basic training!

00:23:14.960 --> 00:23:17.263
- Younki, calm down.
- We can't get better like this!

00:23:17.329 --> 00:23:19.331
We're betting our lives on this!

00:23:23.836 --> 00:23:25.271
Excuse me, Mr. Azuma.

00:23:25.871 --> 00:23:27.506
Would you consider

00:23:27.573 --> 00:23:31.410
adding something
more practical to the lesson?

00:23:32.611 --> 00:23:34.380
We don't have time to fight.

00:23:35.748 --> 00:23:40.486
You guys only complain.
It's so annoying, you losers!

00:23:42.488 --> 00:23:45.357
There's a Japanese saying
that means losers have big mouths.

00:23:45.791 --> 00:23:47.760
You lost the match

00:23:47.826 --> 00:23:51.330
then when you've run far enough,
you bark that you didn't lose.

00:23:51.397 --> 00:23:52.998
That's what cowards do.

00:23:54.566 --> 00:23:56.302
Pointless basic training?

00:23:57.536 --> 00:24:00.072
Top artists perform on stage
for over three hours.

00:24:00.139 --> 00:24:02.608
To sing, dance, and manage
your facial expression perfectly

00:24:02.675 --> 00:24:04.944
you need athletic-level stamina.

00:24:05.010 --> 00:24:06.712
You understand that, of course.

00:24:07.446 --> 00:24:09.748
To achieve perfect performances

00:24:09.815 --> 00:24:13.018
they've gone through a hell
that no one sees

00:24:13.585 --> 00:24:15.587
that's why they can be the best.

00:24:16.221 --> 00:24:19.224
Yet you say you bet your lives
on it at that level.

00:24:20.059 --> 00:24:21.126
Don't make me laugh.

00:24:25.998 --> 00:24:29.468
Even if you make a frantic effort,
only one in 100,000 gets rewarded.

00:24:30.069 --> 00:24:34.139
The remaining 99,999 losers

00:24:35.240 --> 00:24:37.643
just complain from afar
and fade away.

00:24:38.110 --> 00:24:39.678
Just like you guys now.

00:24:49.855 --> 00:24:54.226
Don't waste your youth
for an unattainable dream.

00:24:58.197 --> 00:25:01.000
There are plenty
of easier ways to live.

00:25:02.167 --> 00:25:03.435
Think it over carefully.

00:25:34.299 --> 00:25:35.300
I want to...

00:25:37.236 --> 00:25:38.637
debut as soon as I can.

00:25:41.006 --> 00:25:42.674
I am stupid.

00:25:44.710 --> 00:25:46.211
Even if you say it's a dream

00:25:48.080 --> 00:25:49.248
I still can't give up.

00:25:51.850 --> 00:25:53.018
I am stupid!

00:25:55.587 --> 00:25:56.822
That's why...

00:25:58.590 --> 00:26:00.592
I want to chase
an absurdly huge dream!

00:26:28.353 --> 00:26:31.857
It's not like I said
I don't want to do basic training.

00:26:37.062 --> 00:26:39.565
One hundred squats and 100 push-ups.

00:26:40.466 --> 00:26:41.700
Let's do our best.

00:26:59.151 --> 00:27:01.253
Are you going to abandon us now?

00:27:01.320 --> 00:27:02.788
- You'll run away alone?
- Traitor!

00:27:02.855 --> 00:27:05.290
Are you okay with ruining our lives?

00:27:10.729 --> 00:27:14.133
You're depressed, genius producer.

00:27:15.667 --> 00:27:20.272
You drink outside because you want
someone to talk to you. So adorable!

00:27:20.339 --> 00:27:23.041
As if. I'm just broke.

00:27:24.576 --> 00:27:27.112
- Wait!
- What?

00:27:37.022 --> 00:27:40.659
99,999 losers, huh?

00:27:41.627 --> 00:27:43.195
Well said.

00:27:46.231 --> 00:27:50.802
You and I are one of them.
Ruff, ruff!

00:27:53.805 --> 00:27:58.810
But we try to break out of it,
struggling, striving.

00:28:00.345 --> 00:28:01.813
Just like the boys.

00:28:03.215 --> 00:28:04.383
Shut up.

00:28:04.917 --> 00:28:07.019
I've stopped the pointless struggle.

00:28:07.653 --> 00:28:09.855
I'll continue to struggle

00:28:10.355 --> 00:28:11.924
for the boys' future!

00:28:13.825 --> 00:28:16.762
It's for your own selfish reasons,
you debt-ridden CEO.

00:28:17.462 --> 00:28:19.631
Okay, let's drink today!

00:28:33.178 --> 00:28:34.346
Kun?

00:28:36.415 --> 00:28:37.716
He's asleep.

00:28:40.953 --> 00:28:42.154
Kun?

00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:56.435
A Japanese song?

00:28:57.035 --> 00:28:59.304
Why does he listen to a song so old?

00:29:05.210 --> 00:29:07.512
Oh, no! What time is it?

00:29:08.080 --> 00:29:09.214
Eleven o'clock.

00:29:09.314 --> 00:29:10.349
I need to go!

00:29:10.916 --> 00:29:13.552
Go? Where are you going?

00:29:30.969 --> 00:29:32.671
What time is it now?

00:29:32.738 --> 00:29:35.207
You know what time it is?
Don't think an apology is enough!

00:29:35.274 --> 00:29:36.642
Does he work part-time here?

00:29:36.708 --> 00:29:38.010
Go to work at once!

00:29:39.511 --> 00:29:41.013
Please don't mind him.

00:29:51.023 --> 00:29:52.924
Who's that shady-looking guy?

00:29:56.295 --> 00:29:57.496
Money?

00:29:58.363 --> 00:30:00.866
I'll send the money for you.
Don't worry.

00:30:00.932 --> 00:30:01.933
Okay.

00:30:02.034 --> 00:30:03.535
"Send money?"

00:30:05.237 --> 00:30:06.538
Send money?

00:30:06.638 --> 00:30:08.407
Anyway, this is no good!

00:30:08.507 --> 00:30:10.876
Kun works part-time after practice

00:30:10.942 --> 00:30:13.679
and he gave money
to a shady-looking guy.

00:30:13.745 --> 00:30:15.414
Just calm down.

00:30:16.281 --> 00:30:18.483
Could Kun be blackmailed?

00:30:19.451 --> 00:30:21.320
Or is he using drugs?

00:30:21.420 --> 00:30:25.724
Covering up a crime?
No, maybe they're spies.

00:30:26.391 --> 00:30:27.726
So, what was that?

00:30:28.360 --> 00:30:29.995
He paid for information?

00:30:30.062 --> 00:30:32.597
So there will be a shootout
at the pier tonight.

00:30:34.733 --> 00:30:37.536
Oh, no. I must go to rescue him.

00:30:38.470 --> 00:30:41.273
Anyway, I'll go to check on Kun.

00:30:43.975 --> 00:30:45.944
Her imagination is crazy.

00:30:46.011 --> 00:30:48.180
She's the type
to stay cooped up alone.

00:30:52.784 --> 00:30:54.252
What's this? It's dirty.

00:30:54.820 --> 00:30:55.921
Oh, it's Kun's.

00:30:57.389 --> 00:31:01.626
Actually, Kun's parents got divorced,
and he was sent to a children's home.

00:31:02.094 --> 00:31:05.163
He was aiming
to become a professional footballer.

00:31:06.031 --> 00:31:07.599
He got injured and gave up, though.

00:31:09.134 --> 00:31:10.502
A children's home?

00:31:11.103 --> 00:31:14.740
Anyway, if he's working part-time,
we must make him quit.

00:31:15.107 --> 00:31:19.111
If someone who wants to debut at once
has to work part-time for money

00:31:19.177 --> 00:31:20.779
there must be a reason, right?

00:31:24.583 --> 00:31:26.351
What the heck?

00:31:26.418 --> 00:31:29.154
The hospital said
the surgical fee wasn't deposited!

00:31:29.254 --> 00:31:32.824
I gave you the surgical fee!
Where did it go?

00:31:32.924 --> 00:31:34.526
Sorry, I'm also in debt

00:31:34.626 --> 00:31:36.628
and I'm in trouble.

00:31:37.562 --> 00:31:42.234
I'm going to send the money
to the hospital. Trust me.

00:31:42.334 --> 00:31:45.003
I'm your dad, after all.

00:31:46.037 --> 00:31:47.572
Don't be ridiculous, you jerk!

00:31:47.639 --> 00:31:48.974
Stop, Kun!

00:31:49.274 --> 00:31:51.176
- Minase?
- Don't punch him!

00:31:51.777 --> 00:31:54.479
- You can't debut if you're arrested.
- But he--

00:31:54.579 --> 00:31:56.214
No violence!

00:31:56.681 --> 00:31:58.884
Or your dream will be over!

00:32:12.597 --> 00:32:15.167
Well, take care. See you.

00:32:15.667 --> 00:32:17.202
My beloved son.

00:32:27.179 --> 00:32:30.449
Wow, a story like a Korean drama!

00:32:30.549 --> 00:32:33.819
Don't say it like that!
Kun is seriously worried.

00:32:34.186 --> 00:32:35.754
It's none of my business.

00:32:36.421 --> 00:32:38.990
You are their manager,
but I am a producer.

00:32:39.391 --> 00:32:41.626
I can't be bothered
with their private lives.

00:32:42.561 --> 00:32:45.063
You are horrible.

00:32:49.067 --> 00:32:51.470
Someone who doesn't understand
other people's pain

00:32:51.536 --> 00:32:54.306
can't move people's hearts.

00:32:54.840 --> 00:32:57.175
I can't work with someone like that.

00:32:57.275 --> 00:32:59.511
Fire me right now, then.

00:32:59.911 --> 00:33:02.347
I'm not doing this
because I want to anyway.

00:33:06.985 --> 00:33:08.854
Ms. Nam, why did you hire him?

00:33:10.622 --> 00:33:11.623
Just wait and see.

00:33:12.224 --> 00:33:15.994
Our genius is pretty empathetic.

00:33:24.569 --> 00:33:26.805
More basic training today?

00:33:28.240 --> 00:33:32.210
Basic! Basic...

00:33:33.245 --> 00:33:34.746
How many times did I say it?

00:33:34.813 --> 00:33:37.015
Superficial and following the crowd.

00:33:37.115 --> 00:33:38.250
What's that?

00:33:40.352 --> 00:33:42.487
Hey, is Kun here?

00:33:46.124 --> 00:33:47.826
Who are you, old guy?

00:33:47.926 --> 00:33:48.960
The manager of the place

00:33:49.027 --> 00:33:50.495
- where Kun works part-time at.
- What?

00:33:50.562 --> 00:33:51.997
He works part-time?

00:33:53.231 --> 00:33:54.900
He didn't tell his colleagues
he's working?

00:33:54.966 --> 00:33:58.703
He gives money to a guy
who looks like a thug all the time.

00:33:58.770 --> 00:34:00.972
Who knows what he does
behind our backs?

00:34:01.640 --> 00:34:02.641
Mr. Azuma!

00:34:06.044 --> 00:34:07.679
Why isn't he here when it matters?

00:34:08.179 --> 00:34:09.180
Where did he go?

00:34:09.247 --> 00:34:10.248
Excuse me.

00:34:11.249 --> 00:34:12.250
Attention, please.

00:34:14.719 --> 00:34:17.422
There's something
we want to tell you.

00:34:18.056 --> 00:34:19.357
It's about Kun.

00:34:25.163 --> 00:34:26.731
Please check again!

00:34:26.831 --> 00:34:29.901
I told you,
she doesn't want to see you.

00:34:30.435 --> 00:34:31.436
Please!

00:34:32.037 --> 00:34:34.706
I am her son.

00:34:34.806 --> 00:34:35.907
I'm very sorry.

00:34:36.741 --> 00:34:38.109
Please leave.

00:34:44.583 --> 00:34:47.218
You're feeling depressed again.

00:34:50.055 --> 00:34:51.523
Hey.

00:34:54.960 --> 00:34:56.895
Mr. Azuma, you're right.

00:35:01.166 --> 00:35:02.567
I can't play football.

00:35:03.768 --> 00:35:04.869
I can't sing

00:35:05.937 --> 00:35:07.205
and I can't dance.

00:35:09.307 --> 00:35:11.276
My own mom is sick, yet...

00:35:16.081 --> 00:35:17.515
I'm not useful in any way.

00:35:20.619 --> 00:35:21.686
I...

00:35:23.788 --> 00:35:24.990
I...

00:35:27.292 --> 00:35:28.526
I've got nothing.

00:35:37.636 --> 00:35:39.537
Return to Korea first.

00:35:42.440 --> 00:35:45.210
I'm borrowing this.

00:36:00.592 --> 00:36:01.960
I'm sorry about my sudden visit.

00:36:02.127 --> 00:36:05.730
My name is Azuma,
and I'm Kun's colleague.

00:36:06.798 --> 00:36:07.799
Work?

00:36:07.899 --> 00:36:10.635
Well, I'm his supervisor.

00:36:11.770 --> 00:36:13.738
So I've heard what happened.

00:36:17.609 --> 00:36:20.111
Are you not going to meet Kun?

00:36:24.783 --> 00:36:26.918
I abandoned him.

00:36:28.787 --> 00:36:29.888
It's too late.

00:36:31.556 --> 00:36:33.958
I have no right to see him.

00:36:37.362 --> 00:36:42.500
True. You abandoned your young son.
You are a horrible mom.

00:36:43.401 --> 00:36:44.402
But this...

00:36:53.745 --> 00:36:55.847
He's still keeping that?

00:36:57.682 --> 00:36:59.651
He's been playing football,
apparently.

00:37:00.351 --> 00:37:01.953
He wanted to be a national player

00:37:02.387 --> 00:37:05.490
and stand in the National Stadium
in a match against Japan.

00:37:06.458 --> 00:37:08.626
After he got injured
and couldn't play football

00:37:08.927 --> 00:37:11.362
he abruptly changed course
to become a K-pop artist

00:37:11.429 --> 00:37:14.265
and now, he wants to stand at
the National Stadium through music.

00:37:15.133 --> 00:37:17.168
Well, I guess he's devoted.

00:37:17.235 --> 00:37:20.105
I do think
there are other ways to do it.

00:37:21.306 --> 00:37:22.307
Well, anyway...

00:37:23.374 --> 00:37:28.379
He was separated from his mom,
and he wants her to find him.

00:37:30.014 --> 00:37:31.750
If he had thought you were horrible

00:37:32.383 --> 00:37:33.685
would he have gone this far?

00:37:35.487 --> 00:37:39.290
Would he have carried this
with him all the time

00:37:39.491 --> 00:37:41.459
until it's so worn out?

00:37:51.302 --> 00:37:53.772
My son's dad is a gambling addict.

00:37:54.973 --> 00:37:57.942
His debt got bigger and bigger.

00:38:00.411 --> 00:38:04.149
Finally, the debt collectors
showed up uninvited at our home.

00:38:05.617 --> 00:38:09.721
I tried to bring my son
to flee to Japan

00:38:10.622 --> 00:38:11.656
but he found us.

00:38:11.723 --> 00:38:15.794
Don't be ridiculous!
Don't think you two can escape alone!

00:38:15.860 --> 00:38:17.162
Stop!

00:38:18.696 --> 00:38:21.966
So I fled to Japan on my own

00:38:22.934 --> 00:38:24.235
and abandoned my son.

00:38:26.070 --> 00:38:29.140
I really wanted to live
with my son, but...

00:38:30.141 --> 00:38:31.176
I was too scared.

00:38:32.744 --> 00:38:34.512
But a year ago

00:38:35.480 --> 00:38:37.515
that man showed up again.

00:38:40.518 --> 00:38:42.253
That was when I first found out

00:38:43.721 --> 00:38:45.757
that right after our divorce

00:38:46.491 --> 00:38:49.160
our son was sent
to a children's home.

00:38:50.428 --> 00:38:52.997
He didn't know anyone at that place

00:38:54.532 --> 00:38:56.367
and he had been alone the whole time.

00:39:00.271 --> 00:39:04.609
That was when I was diagnosed
with this disease.

00:39:06.845 --> 00:39:08.079
It was cancer.

00:39:10.348 --> 00:39:11.349
This is...

00:39:14.619 --> 00:39:17.055
the punishment I deserve
for abandoning my son.

00:39:18.590 --> 00:39:21.125
That's why...

00:39:24.529 --> 00:39:27.031
I'm not worthy of meeting my son.

00:39:28.766 --> 00:39:32.170
Kun heard that his mom had a disease

00:39:32.237 --> 00:39:35.039
so he wanted to earn money
to pay for her surgical fee.

00:39:35.773 --> 00:39:38.243
Is that why he works part-time?

00:39:38.810 --> 00:39:41.179
The reason he wants to debut
as soon as possible

00:39:41.779 --> 00:39:43.114
is because if he gets the money

00:39:43.181 --> 00:39:46.417
he can let his mom have
the surgery as soon as possible.

00:39:47.785 --> 00:39:48.887
Kun...

00:39:49.487 --> 00:39:50.855
Why didn't he tell us?

00:39:54.292 --> 00:39:59.397
I couldn't make him feel like
he could open up to me either.

00:40:01.266 --> 00:40:02.800
I'm a terrible CEO.

00:40:04.535 --> 00:40:07.772
But now, we know everything.

00:40:08.473 --> 00:40:12.644
What really matters
is what we're going to do now. Right?

00:40:15.179 --> 00:40:17.482
Well, I'm just a stranger

00:40:17.949 --> 00:40:19.784
so I have no right to say anything.

00:40:20.652 --> 00:40:21.653
But...

00:40:23.021 --> 00:40:24.722
Although Kun was abandoned
by his parents

00:40:25.823 --> 00:40:29.427
he still continues
to make an effort to see you.

00:40:30.295 --> 00:40:34.632
I think
you have a responsibility to face it.

00:40:36.668 --> 00:40:38.937
Although the burden
is too heavy for you

00:40:40.972 --> 00:40:43.508
it doesn't mean you should run away
from someone you love.

00:40:44.275 --> 00:40:47.345
- Are you going to abandon us now?
- You'll run away alone?

00:40:50.048 --> 00:40:51.449
It's tough...

00:40:53.618 --> 00:40:55.720
but you'll regret it if you run away.

00:40:58.690 --> 00:41:00.058
That's what I think.

00:41:10.635 --> 00:41:11.703
After everything...

00:41:13.938 --> 00:41:16.541
I cannot cause him any more trouble.

00:41:18.076 --> 00:41:19.344
From now on...

00:41:21.512 --> 00:41:23.848
I want him to live the way he wants.

00:41:25.350 --> 00:41:27.085
I want him to live freely.

00:41:29.887 --> 00:41:33.658
I want him to stay out of my life.

00:41:37.495 --> 00:41:39.430
Please tell Kun that.

00:41:53.444 --> 00:41:54.545
Welcome back.

00:41:57.548 --> 00:41:58.916
They're waiting for you.

00:42:01.953 --> 00:42:03.054
Raise your legs higher!

00:42:03.121 --> 00:42:05.089
Five, six, seven, eight.

00:42:05.156 --> 00:42:09.894
One, two, three, four,
five, and six, and seven, and eight.

00:42:09.961 --> 00:42:11.996
One, two, three, and four...

00:42:12.063 --> 00:42:14.098
- Kun!
- Five...

00:42:15.433 --> 00:42:18.336
- You're late, Kun.
- Welcome back!

00:42:18.736 --> 00:42:23.207
What are you doing so late?

00:42:23.808 --> 00:42:27.078
Let's show your mom
how hard you're working.

00:42:28.079 --> 00:42:30.014
We're all rooting for you.

00:42:30.615 --> 00:42:31.616
Right, guys?

00:42:35.053 --> 00:42:37.855
I had no idea,
and I was harsh on you.

00:42:39.557 --> 00:42:40.925
I'm sorry.

00:42:44.595 --> 00:42:47.131
Talk to us if you're struggling.

00:42:53.771 --> 00:42:54.939
I'm sorry.

00:42:55.606 --> 00:42:56.607
Kun.

00:42:57.708 --> 00:43:01.012
When your mom knows
you're working hard

00:43:01.079 --> 00:43:02.947
towards your dream

00:43:03.347 --> 00:43:07.885
I'm sure she won't worry anymore,
and she's going to get better.

00:43:10.054 --> 00:43:13.691
But with your current level,
your mom won't be satisfied.

00:43:13.791 --> 00:43:16.994
So I guess I'll have to help you out.

00:43:19.764 --> 00:43:21.165
We are...

00:43:23.134 --> 00:43:24.435
friends.

00:43:36.581 --> 00:43:37.682
Everyone...

00:43:50.862 --> 00:43:53.965
But what are we going to show my mom?

00:43:54.432 --> 00:43:55.466
- What?
- What?

00:43:55.533 --> 00:43:56.767
Azuma didn't tell you?

00:43:57.368 --> 00:43:59.303
That jerk!

00:44:12.683 --> 00:44:14.185
It's been a while.

00:44:16.721 --> 00:44:18.923
- We'll do a live performance.
- Live performance?

00:44:19.023 --> 00:44:22.326
The venue
is the Japan National Stadium.

00:44:23.227 --> 00:44:24.862
- National Stadium?
- National Stadium?

00:44:24.929 --> 00:44:27.665
How did you book such a famous venue?

00:44:27.732 --> 00:44:29.000
Just so you know

00:44:29.100 --> 00:44:31.068
we aren't doing it for Kun alone.

00:44:32.503 --> 00:44:37.008
An artist must be able
to move audience's hearts.

00:44:37.608 --> 00:44:40.244
Are you qualified to aim for that?

00:44:40.311 --> 00:44:41.345
Are you worthy

00:44:41.412 --> 00:44:44.148
of staking your future on this dream?

00:44:44.215 --> 00:44:45.449
I'll assess that thoroughly.

00:44:46.184 --> 00:44:47.351
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:44:48.419 --> 00:44:49.420
The song

00:44:49.987 --> 00:44:50.988
is this.

00:44:52.990 --> 00:44:54.158
This is...

00:44:58.596 --> 00:45:00.097
Let the battle begin!

00:45:00.765 --> 00:45:02.200
- Understood!
- Understood!

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:06.170
- One, two, three, four, five, six...
- One, two, three, four, five, six...

00:45:12.410 --> 00:45:13.411
Ready, go.

00:45:13.477 --> 00:45:17.048
From this position,
open up after the first refrain...

00:45:17.548 --> 00:45:20.251
- One, two, three, four
- One, two, three, four

00:45:20.318 --> 00:45:21.919
- five, six, seven, eight.
- five, six, seven, eight.

00:45:22.019 --> 00:45:23.888
- One, two, three, four...
- One, two, three, four...

00:45:25.890 --> 00:45:27.325
Can we wear this?

00:45:27.391 --> 00:45:28.392
Thank you!

00:45:28.459 --> 00:45:31.329
One, two, three, four, five...

00:45:42.440 --> 00:45:43.708
Excuse me.

00:45:45.610 --> 00:45:48.512
My name is Nam,
CEO of Nam Entertainment.

00:45:51.882 --> 00:45:54.485
There's a performance
I'd very much like you to watch today

00:45:54.552 --> 00:45:55.953
so I'm here to invite you.

00:47:16.467 --> 00:47:17.935
This song is...

00:47:18.402 --> 00:47:20.838
Using the song you loved

00:47:20.905 --> 00:47:23.040
they wanted to show you
how much Kun has grown

00:47:23.541 --> 00:47:25.710
His friends arranged it.

00:48:45.189 --> 00:48:46.557
This is...

00:49:08.446 --> 00:49:09.647
Ta-da!

00:49:15.986 --> 00:49:17.354
Peace!

00:49:17.488 --> 00:49:18.889
One, two, three!

00:49:33.904 --> 00:49:35.706
It's warm.

00:49:39.810 --> 00:49:44.315
I'm sorry, the level of performance
is still very far from professional.

00:49:44.982 --> 00:49:48.752
The steps are unsteady,
and they aren't in sync.

00:49:49.887 --> 00:49:53.424
But Kun is doing everything he can
to convey his love

00:49:53.724 --> 00:49:55.759
to someone precious.

00:49:56.560 --> 00:49:59.363
His friends are working together

00:49:59.430 --> 00:50:02.967
to help him deliver his love
in the best way possible.

00:51:33.290 --> 00:51:35.626
He has grown so much.

00:51:38.295 --> 00:51:43.300
Thanks to you, Mr. Azuma,
I've been able to face it properly.

00:51:45.002 --> 00:51:46.770
I can face his love...

00:51:50.140 --> 00:51:51.875
and face myself, too.

00:52:11.128 --> 00:52:12.663
Thank you so much for yesterday.

00:52:13.497 --> 00:52:16.000
Kun, you've grown so well

00:52:16.767 --> 00:52:21.438
and you're surrounded
by so many wonderful friends.

00:52:22.139 --> 00:52:23.974
I was really happy.

00:52:25.676 --> 00:52:26.844
Mom...

00:52:28.145 --> 00:52:29.546
I'm glad!

00:52:38.088 --> 00:52:40.424
I assessed your potential as artists

00:52:41.058 --> 00:52:43.594
based on your performance yesterday.

00:52:46.196 --> 00:52:48.165
For a group of losers like you

00:52:49.199 --> 00:52:51.869
if you're aiming to be
the one winner out of 100,000

00:52:52.636 --> 00:52:54.004
it's too reckless.

00:52:54.605 --> 00:52:56.740
Impossible. It's absurd.

00:53:00.477 --> 00:53:01.712
But...

00:53:06.050 --> 00:53:09.319
If we're doing it,
we're going global.

00:53:11.755 --> 00:53:13.557
What? Global?

00:53:14.491 --> 00:53:15.526
Which world?

00:53:17.828 --> 00:53:19.863
I'm sorry, everyone!

00:53:20.330 --> 00:53:23.867
This guy is a bit slow
and difficult to understand.

00:53:24.268 --> 00:53:27.304
To sum up,
he's saying, "Let's do our best."

00:53:29.807 --> 00:53:32.176
That's what you mean?
You're being roundabout!

00:53:32.276 --> 00:53:35.079
Wait... You've got to understand!

00:53:35.145 --> 00:53:36.880
Say it properly!

00:53:41.985 --> 00:53:46.223
I swear I will fill up
the Japan National Stadium!

00:53:59.937 --> 00:54:01.805
That's 80,000 people.

00:54:03.207 --> 00:54:05.008
If you can fill
the Japan National Stadium

00:54:05.075 --> 00:54:06.744
I'll do anything you say.

00:54:08.545 --> 00:54:09.546
But...

00:54:12.716 --> 00:54:13.984
Let's go

00:54:15.152 --> 00:54:16.487
to the dream stage.

00:54:18.489 --> 00:54:20.657
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

00:54:20.724 --> 00:54:22.392
You guys are loud.

00:54:22.993 --> 00:54:25.395
Let's go!

00:54:26.730 --> 00:54:28.365
Lend you the Japan National Stadium?

00:54:28.465 --> 00:54:31.268
Your company's artist
will perform there, right?

00:54:31.335 --> 00:54:34.805
30 minutes before you bring in
the equipment will be enough.

00:54:34.872 --> 00:54:36.240
Would you lend it to us?

00:54:36.940 --> 00:54:38.208
For free.

00:54:38.842 --> 00:54:40.210
I see.

00:54:41.612 --> 00:54:42.913
For free, huh?

00:54:48.118 --> 00:54:50.120
You're banned from the music industry
due to the big scandal

00:54:50.220 --> 00:54:51.922
and caused our company huge trouble

00:54:51.989 --> 00:54:53.423
now you want the venue for free?

00:54:53.524 --> 00:54:54.725
Don't be ridiculous.

00:55:01.532 --> 00:55:03.167
It has to be
the Japan National Stadium.

00:55:03.801 --> 00:55:05.068
I beg you.

00:55:05.836 --> 00:55:07.104
Leave.

00:55:10.874 --> 00:55:12.176
I see.

00:55:12.843 --> 00:55:16.647
You were my boss in the past,
so I assumed you'd help me.

00:55:16.713 --> 00:55:18.015
But I guess not.

00:55:18.615 --> 00:55:19.983
Then...

00:55:23.053 --> 00:55:24.087
This.

00:55:25.189 --> 00:55:28.525
I wonder how long I should keep it
in my tiny chest.

00:55:29.126 --> 00:55:30.694
My respected senior

00:55:30.794 --> 00:55:32.529
it's evidence of an embezzlement

00:55:32.596 --> 00:55:34.264
so bold that it earned my respect.

00:55:36.900 --> 00:55:39.670
Ms. Nam, Mr. Azuma...

00:55:40.103 --> 00:55:41.672
I told you to wait and see.

00:55:41.772 --> 00:55:43.674
That's who he is.

00:55:43.941 --> 00:55:45.375
Ready, go!

00:55:45.976 --> 00:55:50.747
- One, two, three, four
- One, two, three, four

00:55:50.814 --> 00:55:54.218
- five, six, seven...
- five, six, seven...

00:55:55.886 --> 00:55:57.221
Mr. Choi.

00:55:58.522 --> 00:55:59.656
Please have a look.

00:56:11.168 --> 00:56:12.402
I must not let this go

00:56:12.903 --> 00:56:14.338
because he's a murderer.

00:56:24.114 --> 00:56:25.415
To make their dreams come true

00:56:25.482 --> 00:56:26.650
they go all out
to support each other.

00:56:26.717 --> 00:56:28.652
That's what our team
is proud of.